properties.Name: Ben Vorlich
properties.Comments: 1974 gives the trig position from an incorrect reading of the 1" map; 1984 and 1990 give a similar GR, but all three editions give the 3092'/943m height of the spot to the north

properties.Name: Meall Garbh
properties.Comments: 1891: 3200' ap, Mr Colin Phillip's aneroid. 1921: 'Mr Colin Phillip: [3145 (W. top), J.G.I.: another well-marked top, ?m to E (dip between, 50-75ft) was made 10ft less'

properties.Name: Meall Buidhe
properties.Comments: 1891: Garbh Mheall; 1921-1969: Meall Buidhe (Garbh Mheall); 1974: Meall Buidhe (Garbh Meall)

properties.Name: Beinn an Dothaidh
properties.Comments: 1969: 4 figure GR is for West top but distance from Bridge of Orchy and 3283' from the early 6" map are consistent with Munro. 1974 gives 3289' from the 1970 6" map

properties.Name: Meall Glas
properties.Comments: 1891: Given as a Top despite being correctly shown as higher than Beinn Chreathaich, see below

properties.Name: Stob Dearg (Buachaille Etive Mor)
properties.Comments: GR of highest point (NN222542) not given until 1997; c.150m SW of summit cairn at NN223543

properties.Name: Stob Coire Sgreamhach
properties.Comments: 1891: Stob Coire Sgrenach; 1921-1969: Beinn Fhada: Stob Coire Sgreamhach; 1974: Beinn Fhada-Stob Coire Sgriodain

properties.Name: Stob Coir' an Albannaich
properties.Comments: 2021: Stob Coire an Albannaich; spelt Coir' on all maps

properties.Name: An Gearanach
properties.Comments: 1933 footnote explains the 1921 move to An Garbhanach as a mistake, and estimates the heights as 3240' and 3230'

properties.Name: A' Bhuidheanach Bheag
properties.Comments: 1891: Fuar Bheinn. Listed as a Top below Meall a' Chaorainn (hill 393) despite being correctly recorded as higher.

properties.Name: Carn Bhac
properties.Comments: 1891: Top of Coire Bhourneasg; 1921-1974: Carn Bhac, NE Top

properties.Name: An Socach
properties.Comments: 1891-1969: An Socach (West End); 1974: An Socach�West End; 1981-1990: An Socach�West summit

properties.Name: Sgor an Lochain Uaine
properties.Comments: 1891: Sgor an Lochain Uaine, Carn Toul; 1921-1969: Sgor an Lochan Uaine (The Angel's Peak); 1974: Sgor an Lochan Uaine

properties.Name: Monadh Mor
properties.Comments: 1891-1969: 2� miles SW by S (1891 : SW) of Carin Toul - could be 1113 m or 1110 m top. Height 3651' (1113m) in 1891-1969 Tables.

properties.Name: Beinn a' Chaorainn
properties.Comments: 1891: Beinn a' Chaoruinn, Middle Top; 1974: Beinn a' Chaoruinn (Centre Top)

properties.Name: Beinn Teallach
properties.Comments: 1984: promoted in Addendum on p.10 of theTables

properties.Name: The Saddle
properties.Comments: 1891-1974: distances of other tops from summit consistent with this top rather than trig point being the Munro

properties.Name: Gulvain [Gaor Bheinn]
properties.Comments: 1891: Gulvain, North Top; 1921-1974: Gaor Bheinn or Gulvain, N Top; 1981-1990: Gaor Bheinn (or Gulvain); 1997-2021: Gulvain

properties.Name: Sgurr nan Ceathramhnan [Sgurr nan Ceathreamhnan]
properties.Comments: 1891: Sgurr nan Caethreamhnan, E. Top; 1921-1997: Sgurr nan Ceathreamhnan

properties.Name: Sail Chaorainn
properties.Comments: 1891: Tigh Mor, SSW top; 1921-1974: Tigh Mor na Seilge SSW Top

properties.Name: Maoile Lunndaidh
properties.Comments: 1891: Maoile Lunndaich. Made the Munro even though height given as 1ft lower than the southern summit, hill 891 (1.2ft lower on the 1883 6" map). This was corrected in 1921.

properties.Name: Ruadh Stac Mor
properties.Comments: 1974: NH021758 is taken from the 2850' contour on the inaccurate 1" map. The 3014' height comes from the trig on the 1967 6" map correctly shown at NH018756.

properties.Name: Beinn Tarsuinn
properties.Comments: Mentioned in 1933 as a probable Munro and listed in 1953 and 1969 without being properly included. See worksheet for A' Mhaighdean

properties.Name: Meall Gorm
properties.Comments: 1891: Meallan Rairigidh; 1921-1974: Meall Gorm NW Top

properties.Name: Sgurr a' Mhadaidh
properties.Comments: See named worksheet for discussion of 1974 grid reference

properties.Name: Sgurr Mhic Choinnich
properties.Comments: 1921 -1981: Sgurr Mhic Coinnich. Comment "new top" in 1921 Tables. Follows appearance of 3107' spot on 1903 6" map.

properties.Name: Sgurr Alasdair
properties.Comments: 1891: Sgurr Alaisdair (S.W. Peak), 3255' aneroid measurement equal to 992.0m GNSS survey height

properties.Name: Blabheinn [Bla Bheinn]
properties.Comments: 1891: Blath Bheinn (Blaven), N Top; 1921-1969: Blaven; 1974-1990: Bla Bheinn (Blaven); 1997: Bla Bheinn
